Your CSS code is already taking care of the displaying part. You don&#39;t need to do that again with JavaScript. What you are looking for is the classList.toggle() method. This will add and remove the .reveal-content class on a click event. This is what your JavaScript code should be:
```
var div = document.querySelector(&quot;div&quot;);
var button = document.getElementById(&quot;btn-reveal&quot;);
button.addEventListener(&#39;click&#39;, function () {
   div.classList.toggle(&quot;reveal-content&quot;);
});
```
